On Apr. 1, In accordance with the decision of the next meeting of the Republican special commission, the Uzbek Ministry for the Support of Mahalla and Family sets up the Center for Sponsorship Coordination aimed at delivery of charitable funds to those in need during quarantine. 
 for charitable purposes, a list of single elderly people in need of social protection (single mothers, disabled people, unemployed citizens, people deprived of permanent income due to quarantine, etc.) and low-income families will be compiled.

- Sponsorship Coordination Center: forms a list of volunteers from among those who voluntarily wish to participate in charitable activities;

- introduces a person who wants to provide charity help according to the statement with the total number of people in need, based on the amount of charity, recommends people who need help;

On the territory of Uzexpocenter, the Center for the Coordination of Sponsorship Activities will be located and a special media pool for bloggers and journalists will be created to ensure transparency;

Information about the centers (phone numbers, responsible persons, location, etc.) will be distributed to the general public through the media, social networks and television. Donations from sponsors (with their consent) will be widely publicized.

According to the news on February 3,  in connection with the spread of the new coronavirus, the Ministry of Public Education of Uzbekistan will carry out explanatory work on the prevention of acute respiratory infections, influenza and coronavirus. On the recommendation of the Ministry of Health, public education will carry out explanatory work on the prevention of ARI, influenza and coronavirus. The Agency for Sanitary and Epidemiological Well-being distributed recommendations on the prevention of ARI, influenza and coronavirus:

- often ventilate and disinfect the room, as well as ensure the temperature in the room;
- do not to allow employees and students with clinical symptoms of the disease or high temperature to work and study, as well as ensure their visits to a medical institution;
- carry out regular cleaning and disinfection of restrooms;
- wash hands and observe personal hygiene;
- provide students and staff with medical masks;
- organize seminars with students and staff on coronavirus and preventive measures;

For symptoms of the disease, seek medical attention as soon as possible. Treatment should be carried out only under the supervision of a doctor.

Uzbekistan: Special Republican Commission on Prevention of the Covid-19 Spread authorizes following business to resume their operation as of Apr. 25:

"- Markets for building materials, including business entities involved in retail and wholesale trade in building materials (provided that their area is at least 500 sq.);

- Chain stores of large manufacturers, designed to sell their own products (in compliance with the sanitary standard of 10 square meters per 1 buyer);

- Craftsmen - sale in the places (stores) of products created by them, separate from markets;

- Business entities (of any form of ownership) engaged in the cultivation and sale of seeds and seedlings;

- Points (cash desks) of commercial banks in various facilities;

- Entrepreneurs (regardless of ownership) engaged in the sale of automotive parts;

- Organization for the provision of after-sales service for automobiles, agricultural and construction equipment with an area of at least 1000 square meters. m, as well as entities providing vulcanization services;

- Business entities involved in dry cleaning;

- Notary offices and insurance companies;

- Suspended investment projects and work on the construction of social facilities."

